[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Software planning
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text

[GRAMMAR]
IMPORT_FROM_FILE: en_50716_grammar.sgra

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document is the Software Planning package for the software element of
the railway control and protection system identified below. It is prepared in
accordance with EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.3 (Lifecycle issues and documentation),
and collects the five planning deliverables listed in Table A.1:

  1. Software Quality Assurance Plan (SQAP)
  2. Software Planning Verification Report
  3. Software Configuration Management Plan (SCMP)
  4. Software Verification Plan (SVP)
  5. Software Validation Plan (SValP)

BASIC, SIL_1 through SIL_4 fields classify requirements as M / HR / R / NR / --
per EN 50716:2023 Table A.1. M = Mandatory, HR = Highly Recommended,
R = Recommended, NR = Not Recommended, -- = Not applicable at this level.

Instructions for use:
- UIDs follow convention: SP-xxx.
- Replace every <...> placeholder with project-specific content.
- Delete this instruction block before formal release.
<<<

