[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Software Quality Assurance Plan (SQAP)

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Quality Assurance Plan as required by
EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.3.1. The SQAP defines the software lifecycle,
documentation strategy, organisational structure, and personnel competence
requirements that govern all software activities on this project.
<<<

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Software lifecycle definition

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-010
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Software lifecycle model
STATEMENT: >>>
The software shall be developed in accordance with a defined software lifecycle
conforming to EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.3.2. The lifecycle comprises the following
phases:

  1. Software Requirements Specification
  2. Software Architecture and Design
  3. Software Component Design and Implementation
  4. Software Component Testing
  5. Software Integration and Integration Testing
  6. Overall Software Testing (Validation)
  7. Software Assessment (if required by the applicable CENELEC role)

Each phase shall have documented entry criteria, activities, deliverables,
and exit criteria. Phase completion shall be confirmed by a formal review
before the subsequent phase commences.
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.3.2 – Software lifecycle.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-011
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Software lifecycle deliverables
STATEMENT: >>>
The following documents shall be produced as software lifecycle deliverables
and placed under configuration management:

  - Software Quality Assurance Plan (this document, section 2)
  - Software Planning Verification Report (this document, section 3)
  - Software Configuration Management Plan (this document, section 4)
  - Software Verification Plan (this document, section 5)
  - Software Validation Plan (this document, section 6)
  - Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
  - Software Architecture Specification (SAS)
  - Software Component Design Specification (SCDS)
  - Software Component Test Specification and Report
  - Software Integration Test Specification and Report
  - Software Validation Report
  - Problem Reporting and Resolution Records
<<<
