[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Organisation and independence of roles

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-020
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Organisational roles and responsibilities
STATEMENT: >>>
The following roles are defined for software activities in accordance with
EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.1:

Software Manager:
  <Name>
  Responsibilities: Overall software management; approval of lifecycle
  deliverables; liaison with the system safety assessor and CENELEC assessor.

Software Architect:
  <Name>
  Responsibilities: Software requirements specification; architecture design;
  architecture verification.

Software Developer(s):
  <Name(s)>
  Responsibilities: Component design, implementation, and unit testing.

Software Verifier:
  <Name / Organisation>
  Responsibilities: Independent verification of requirements, design, code,
  and test results at all lifecycle phases.

Software Validator:
  <Name / Organisation>
  Responsibilities: Independent validation of the integrated software against
  the software requirements specification.

CENELEC Assessor (if applicable):
  <Name / Organisation>
  Responsibilities: Independent assessment of software activities and
  deliverables per EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.1.
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
