[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Personnel competence

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-030
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Competence requirements for software roles
STATEMENT: >>>
All persons assigned to software safety activities shall possess competence
appropriate to their role and to the target SIL, as required by
EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.2. Competence shall be evidenced by:

  a) Relevant education or professional qualifications in software engineering
     or a related discipline.
  b) Demonstrable experience in safety-related software development for
     railway or equivalent high-integrity domains.
  c) Knowledge of EN 50716:2023 and any applicable sector standards.
  d) Familiarity with the tools and methods mandated by this plan.
  e) Completion of project-specific induction and training.

Competence records shall be maintained by the Software Manager and shall
be available for review by the CENELEC assessor.
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.2 – Personnel competence.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-031
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Competence of the verifier and validator
STATEMENT: >>>
The Software Verifier and Software Validator shall additionally demonstrate:

  a) Experience in performing independent software verification or validation
     in railway or equivalent safety-critical domains.
  b) Knowledge of applicable verification and validation techniques
     (static analysis, test design, formal methods as appropriate to the SIL).
  c) Independence from the development team as specified in SP-021 and SP-022.

Assessors shall meet the competence requirements of EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.2,
and any applicable national or operator requirements.
<<<
