[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Documentation strategy

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-040
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document control and traceability
STATEMENT: >>>
All software lifecycle documents shall be subject to document control
per EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.3.3:

  a) Each document shall carry a unique identifier, revision number, date,
     author, and approval signature.
  b) Changes to released documents shall follow the change control process
     defined in SP-061.
  c) Bidirectional traceability shall be maintained between:
       - System requirements and software requirements.
       - Software requirements and design artefacts.
       - Design artefacts and source code.
       - Source code and test cases.
       - Test cases and test results.
  d) Traceability evidence shall be included in the Software Validation Plan
     and reported in the Software Validation Report.

Document management system: <tool / shared drive reference>
<<<
