[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Software Planning Verification Report

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Planning Verification Report as required
by EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.3. The planning verification confirms that the
planning documents are complete, consistent, and compliant with the standard
before development activities commence.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-050
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Scope of planning verification
STATEMENT: >>>
The planning verification shall cover all planning documents produced for this
project:

  - Software Quality Assurance Plan (SQAP, section 2)
  - Software Configuration Management Plan (SCMP, section 4)
  - Software Verification Plan (SVP, section 5)
  - Software Validation Plan (SValP, section 6)

For each planning document, the verification shall check:

  a) Compliance with the requirements of EN 50716:2023 Clause 5.3.
  b) Internal consistency of the plan contents.
  c) Consistency between the individual plans (e.g. the verification methods
     in the SVP are supported by the tools listed in the SCMP).
  d) Adequacy of the independence arrangements for the target SIL.
  e) Completeness: all required plan elements are present.
<<<
