VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.3 – Configuration management.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-061
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Change and modification control
STATEMENT: >>>
All changes to software configuration items after the initial baseline shall
follow the change and modification control process defined in EN 50716:2023,
Clause 6.6:

  1. Change Request (CR) raised, assigned a unique identifier, and recorded.
  2. Impact analysis performed: technical, safety, and schedule impact assessed.
  3. Safety impact classification assigned: Safety-Critical / Non-Safety-Critical.
  4. CR reviewed and approved by the Software Manager; safety-critical CRs
     also reviewed by the Software Verifier.
  5. Change implemented, tested, and verified in accordance with the SVP.
  6. New software baseline created, documented, and released.
  7. CR closed and resolution recorded.

Regression testing scope shall be commensurate with the safety impact of the
change.

Change request tracking system: <tool / document reference>
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 6.6 – Modification of software.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-062
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Baseline management
STATEMENT: >>>
A software configuration baseline shall be established at the completion of
each lifecycle phase and at each formal release. Each baseline shall be
identified by:

  - Unique baseline identifier (e.g. SW-BL-001)
  - Date and the exact revision of each SCI included
  - Reference to the phase exit review record or release note
  - Hash or checksum of the released artefacts (where applicable)

The software validation baseline shall be the sole basis for the released
software product. Any deviation from the validated baseline shall be treated
as a change under SP-061.
<<<
