[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Software Verification Plan (SVP)

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Verification Plan as required by
EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.3. The SVP defines the scope, objectives, methods,
and independence arrangements for software verification activities at each
lifecycle phase.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-070
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Verification scope and objectives
STATEMENT: >>>
Software verification shall be performed at each lifecycle phase to confirm
that the outputs of that phase are correct, complete, and consistent with
the phase inputs. Verification shall cover:

  Phase 1 – Requirements Verification:
    Confirm the Software Requirements Specification is complete, unambiguous,
    testable, and consistent with system requirements.

  Phase 2 – Architecture Verification:
    Confirm the software architecture satisfies safety requirements and is
    amenable to the chosen design and testing methods.

  Phase 3 – Component Verification:
    Confirm detailed design is consistent with architecture; confirm source
    code conforms to design and coding standard.

  Phase 4 – Test Verification:
    Confirm test specifications cover all requirements; confirm test results
    are complete and correct.

Verification activities and their results shall be documented in phase-specific
Verification Reports.
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.3 – Software verification plan.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-071
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Verification independence
STATEMENT: >>>
Verification activities shall be performed with independence from development
activities at the level required by SP-021. The verifier shall not verify
artefacts they authored.

For SIL 3 and SIL 4, verification of safety-critical components shall be
conducted using formal review (inspection or structured walk-through) with
at least two independent participants in addition to the author.

Verification records shall include the name and independence evidence for
each verifier.
<<<
BASIC: --
SIL_1: R
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: M
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.1 – Independence requirements.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-072
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Verification methods
STATEMENT: >>>
The following verification methods shall be applied, selected according to
the lifecycle phase and target SIL per EN 50716:2023, Table A.1:

  Inspection:         Review of documents and artefacts against checklists.
                      Applied at all phases and all SIL levels.

  Walk-through:       Author-led structured review with independent
                      participants. Applied at SIL 2 and above for
                      architecture and design.

  Formal review:      Structured inspection per defined procedure.
                      Applied at SIL 3 and above for safety-critical items.

  Static analysis:    Automated analysis of source code (coding standard
                      compliance, control flow, data flow, metrics).
                      Applied at SIL 2 and above.

  Simulation:         Model-based or rapid-prototype verification of
                      requirements or architecture behaviour.
                      Applied where formal analysis is impractical.

  Formal proof:       Mathematical proof of correctness for critical
                      algorithms or properties.
                      Applied at SIL 4 where HR or M per Table A.1.

The selection and rationale for each method applied shall be documented in
the phase verification report.
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.1 – Verification techniques.

