[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Software Validation Plan (SValP)

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Validation Plan as required by
EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.3. The SValP defines the scope, objectives,
independence arrangements, and support tool strategy for software validation.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-080
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Validation scope and objectives
STATEMENT: >>>
Software validation shall confirm that the integrated software, on the target
hardware or a representative test environment, satisfies the Software
Requirements Specification and is fit for its intended railway application.

Validation shall include:

  a) Review of all lifecycle deliverables for completeness and consistency.
  b) Confirmation of full bidirectional traceability from system requirements
     to test evidence (as defined in SP-040).
  c) Execution of the validation test suite defined in the Software Validation
     Test Specification on the target or equivalent environment.
  d) Evaluation of all open problem reports and confirmation that none remain
     open that could affect safety or fitness for purpose.
  e) Confirmation that all software lifecycle activities have been performed
     in accordance with the applicable plans.

Validation results shall be documented in the Software Validation Report.
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 5.3 – Software validation plan.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-081
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Validation independence
STATEMENT: >>>
Validation shall be performed with independence from development activities
at the level required by SP-022. The validator shall not have authored the
software requirements, design, or implementation being validated.

The validation environment (hardware, operating system, communication
interfaces) shall be representative of the operational target environment.
Any deviations shall be documented and their impact on validity assessed.

Validation environment description: <hardware platform, OS, interfaces>
Deviations from operational environment: <none / list deviations>
Impact assessment reference: <document ID or "N/A">
<<<
