[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SP-082
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Support tools strategy
STATEMENT: >>>
Support tools used during software development, verification, and validation
shall be managed in accordance with EN 50716:2023, Clause 6.7. Tools are
classified as follows:

  Class T1: Tool output is not used directly in the executable software and
            tool errors cannot affect software safety.
  Class T2: Tool validates requirements, design, or test results; errors
            could cause an undetected unsafe failure.
  Class T3: Tool output is included in the safety-related executable; errors
            could directly cause a failure.

Tool classification and qualification status:

  Tool                      | Version   | Class | Qualification
  --------------------------|-----------|-------|---------------------------
  <Compiler>                | <x.y.z>   | T3    | Required – per Cl. 6.7
  <Static analysis tool>    | <x.y.z>   | T2    | Required – per Cl. 6.7
  <Test execution framework>| <x.y.z>   | T2    | Required – per Cl. 6.7
  <Coverage measurement>    | <x.y.z>   | T2    | Required – per Cl. 6.7
  <Model checker / prover>  | <x.y.z>   | T2    | Required – per Cl. 6.7
  <Requirements tool>       | <x.y.z>   | T2    | Required – per Cl. 6.7
  <Version control>         | <x.y.z>   | T1    | Not required

T3 and T2 tools shall be qualified before use in safety-related activities.
Qualification shall be performed using one or more of:
  a) Vendor-supplied certificate of tool qualification.
  b) Execution of a tool validation test suite against known inputs.
  c) Cross-checking by a diverse independent tool.

Tool qualification records shall be maintained under configuration management
(SP-060) and referenced from the Software Validation Report.
<<<
